entry.content:
封面来源：ChatGPT-4 DALL·E



Cover Art: ChatGPT-4 DALL·E



摘要：通过将机器学习应用于基于情绪的准确且经济高效的照片分类，作者引入了从大量新闻照片样本中获得的日度市场级投资者情绪指数（照片悲观度）。与行为模型一致，照片悲观情绪可以预测市场回报逆转和交易量。在恐慌情绪高涨期间，这种关系在套利限制高的股票中最为强烈。此外，本文研究了照片悲观度和新闻文本中蕴含的悲观主义在预测股票收益方面是互为补充还是相互替代，并发现了两者相互替代的证据。



Abstract: By applying machine learning to accurate and cost-effective sentiment-based photo classification, the authors introduce a daily market-level investor sentiment index (photo pessimism) derived from a large sample of news photos. Consistent with behavioral models, photo pessimism predicts market return reversals and trading volume. This relationship is strongest among stocks with high limits to arbitrage during periods of heightened fear. Additionally, this paper examines whether photo pessimism and pessimism embedded in news text are complements or substitutes in predicting stock returns, finding evidence of substitution.



引用：Obaid, K., & Pukthuanthong, K. (2022). A picture is worth a thousand words: Measuring investor sentiment by combining machine learning and photos from news. Journal of Financial Economics, 144(1), 273-297.



Citation: Obaid, K., & Pukthuanthong, K. (2022). A picture is worth a thousand words: Measuring investor sentiment by combining machine learning and photos from news. Journal of Financial Economics, 144(1), 273-297.


文献/Paper：
Keywords: Investor sentiment; Behavioral finance; Return predictability; Machine learning; Deep learning; Big data.
Introduction
A good sketch is better than a long speech.
​                                                                        —— Napoleon Bonaparte 

Investor Sentiment
投资者情绪理解及预测市场收益（天气与股市收益$\color{blue}{Hirshleifer\ and\ Shumway,\ 2003}$; 运动情绪与股市收益$\color{blue}{Edmans\ et\ al.,\ 2007JF}$; 媒体情绪$\color{blue}{Tetlock,\ 2007JF}$; 实证模型$\color{blue}{Spiegel,\ 2008}$）和横截面股票收益（$\color{blue}{Baker\ and\ Wurgler,\ 2006}$; $\color{blue}{Kozak\ et\ al.,\ 2018}$）



Investor sentiment helps understand and predict market returns (weather and stock market returns $\color{blue}{Hirshleifer\ and\ Shumway,\ 2003}$; sports sentiment and stock market returns $\color{blue}{Edmans\ et\ al.,\ 2007JF}$; media sentiment $\color{blue}{Tetlock,\ 2007JF}$; empirical models $\color{blue}{Spiegel,\ 2008}$) and cross-sectional stock returns ($\color{blue}{Baker\ and\ Wurgler,\ 2006}$; $\color{blue}{Kozak\ et\ al.,\ 2018}$)


Contributions

（1）展示视觉内容在预测市场收益方面的重要性：

- 构建日度投资者情绪指数，照片悲观度（*PhotoPes*），计算为在给定日期预测为负面的新闻照片的比例；
- *PhotoPes*对第二天的市场回报呈负相关，而与剩余交易周的市场回报率呈正相关；
- 反转凸显了指标对收益的非信息影响；
- 与投资者情绪代理一致，*PhotoPes*预测次日交易量增加，并更好地预测套利限制高股票的收益。

（2）展示如何通过机器学习技术进行大规模照片分类，克服研究金融市场中视觉内容重要性的关键障碍：

- 由于现代技术和对快速信息的需求，图片新闻越来越受欢迎（*Photojournalism has increased in popularity due to modern technology and the demand for quick information.* ）

- 已有研究表明，照片可能比文字更有效地传达情感信息，有鉴于此，作者认为研究从新闻媒体照片中提取的情感与市场活动的关系非常重要（[$\color{blue}{Chemtob\ et\ al.,\ 1999JTS}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1023/A:1024728626505)）；
  - 然而，由于分析照片的复杂性和人工筛选大量照片的成本，类似研究成本高昂、容易出错且繁琐；
  - 依靠**调查或众包网站**（如 Amazon Mechanical Turk、MTurk）评估照片已成为从照片中提取信息的主流方法；经济学家对调查数据也持谨慎态度，因为其主观性过强，无法通过 “客观的外部测量”验证（[$\color{blue}{Vissing-Jorgensen,\ 2003}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/ma.18.3585252)）；另外，[$\color{blue}{Singer\ (2002)}$](https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/document?repid=rep1&type=pdf&doi=99a37f7b5f2b4aa5857efe531fc75ce3fe340ab7)指出，当问题涉及敏感话题且答案取决于受访者的主观意愿时，受访者往往不太愿意认真如实回答问题；
  - 使用**机器学习方法**可以减轻这种担忧（具体而言，作者应用卷积神经网络（CNN）这一常用于照片分类的机器学习技术，对大量新闻照片样本进行了基于情感的准确、可验证且低成本的分类）；

（3）比较了*PhotoPes*和新闻文本中嵌入的悲观情绪的预测能力：

- 实证发现，**新闻照片中的悲观情绪和新闻文字中的悲观情绪可以相互替代**；
- **照片突出时期，照片能从文字中吸引注意力**（在新闻照片绝大多数是负面或正面的时期，新闻照片中的悲观情绪占主导地位。与此相反，当新闻照片是中性或混合性时，文字中蕴含的悲观情绪会占据主导地位）；
- 未有文献从新闻图片中捕捉有关投资者信念的有用和新颖信息的可能性，以及这些信息如何与文本中的信息相互作用；




(1) Demonstrating the importance of visual content in predicting market returns:

- Constructing a daily investor sentiment index, photo pessimism (*PhotoPes*), calculated as the proportion of news photos predicted as negative on a given day;
- *PhotoPes* is negatively correlated with the next day's market returns and positively correlated with market returns for the rest of the trading week;
- The reversal highlights the non-informational impact of the measure on returns;
- Consistent with investor sentiment proxies, *PhotoPes* predicts increased next-day trading volume and better predicts returns of stocks with high limits to arbitrage.

(2) Demonstrating how machine learning techniques enable large-scale photo classification, overcoming a key obstacle to studying the importance of visual content in financial markets:

- Photojournalism has increased in popularity due to modern technology and the demand for quick information.

- Existing research suggests that photos may convey emotional information more effectively than text; accordingly, the authors argue it is important to study the relationship between sentiment extracted from news media photos and market activity ([$\color{blue}{Chemtob\ et\ al.,\ 1999JTS}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1023/A:1024728626505));
  - However, such research is costly, error-prone, and tedious due to the complexity of analyzing photos and the cost of manually screening large volumes of photos;
  - Relying on **surveys or crowdsourcing platforms** (e.g., Amazon Mechanical Turk, MTurk) to evaluate photos has become the mainstream method for extracting information from photos; economists are also cautious about survey data due to its excessive subjectivity and inability to be verified through “objective external measurement” ([$\color{blue}{Vissing-Jorgensen,\ 2003}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/ma.18.3585252)); additionally, [$\color{blue}{Singer\ (2002)}$](https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/document?repid=rep1&type=pdf&doi=99a37f7b5f2b4aa5857efe531fc75ce3fe340ab7) notes that when questions involve sensitive topics and answers depend on respondents' subjective willingness, respondents tend to be less willing to answer honestly;
  - Using **machine learning methods** can alleviate this concern (specifically, the authors apply convolutional neural networks (CNN), a machine learning technique commonly used for photo classification, to perform accurate, verifiable, and low-cost sentiment-based classification of a large sample of news photos);

(3) Comparing the predictive power of *PhotoPes* and pessimism embedded in news text:

- Empirical findings show that **pessimism in news photos and pessimism in news text are substitutes**;
- **During periods when photos are salient, photos capture attention away from text** (during periods when news photos are predominantly negative or positive, pessimism in news photos dominates. In contrast, when news photos are neutral or mixed, pessimism embedded in text dominates);
- No prior literature has explored the possibility of capturing useful and novel information about investor beliefs from news images, or how such information interacts with information in text;


Machine Learning
金融研究人员已接受机器学习（$\color{blue}{Mullainathan\ and\ Spiess,\ 2017JEP}$）

$\color{blue}{Manela\ and\ Moreira\ (2017JFE)}$00268-3/sbref0047)使用机器学习从WSJ文本中构建新闻隐含波动率指数；
$\color{blue}{Buehlmaier\ and\ Whited\ (2018)}$通过分析财务报告构建了财务约束的衡量标准，并表明衡量标准与获得资本和股票收益有关；
机器学习结合金融数据：
  - 预测风险溢价（$\color{blue}{Gu\ et\ al.,\ 2020}$00268-3/sbref0037)）；
  - 寻找真正的风险因素（$\color{blue}{Feng\ et\ al.,\ 2020}$00268-3/sbref0029)）；

机器学习新技术引入→→→分析大量照片可行→→→引入CNN从大量新闻照片样本中构建投资者情绪指数

预训练的 Google Inception (v3) 模型

该模型未经过专门训练识别情绪，但包含大量有关图像的领域知识；
迁移学习（向预训练模型提供由情绪专门标记的额外训练照片样本，并将原始模型的最终全连接层替换为仅含两类感兴趣的新层：消极和积极情绪）；
该模型考虑了照片的多方面：objects、colors、facial expressions，以做出预测；
模型训练后，测试集样本准确率为87.1%；
使用该模型对WSJ照片进行投资者情绪预测→→→使用情绪预测构建日度投资者情绪指数（照片悲观度，PhotoPes）→→→给定日期负面照片所占比例；



Financial researchers have embraced machine learning ($\color{blue}{Mullainathan\ and\ Spiess,\ 2017JEP}$)

$\color{blue}{Manela\ and\ Moreira\ (2017JFE)}$00268-3/sbref0047) use machine learning to construct a news-implied volatility index from WSJ text;
$\color{blue}{Buehlmaier\ and\ Whited\ (2018)}$ construct measures of financial constraints by analyzing financial reports and show these measures relate to access to capital and stock returns;
Machine learning combined with financial data:
  - Predicting risk premia ($\color{blue}{Gu\ et\ al.,\ 2020}$00268-3/sbref0037));
  - Identifying true risk factors ($\color{blue}{Feng\ et\ al.,\ 2020}$00268-3/sbref0029));

Introduction of new ML techniques → analyzing large volumes of photos becomes feasible → introducing CNN to construct an investor sentiment index from a large sample of news photos

Pre-trained Google Inception (v3) model

The model was not specifically trained to recognize sentiment but contains extensive domain knowledge about images;
Transfer learning (providing the pre-trained model with additional training photo samples specifically labeled by sentiment, and replacing the original model's final fully connected layer with a new layer containing only two classes of interest: negative and positive sentiment);
The model considers multiple aspects of photos — objects, colors, facial expressions — to make predictions;
After training, the model achieves 87.1% accuracy on the test set;
Using the model to predict investor sentiment from WSJ photos → constructing a daily investor sentiment index (photo pessimism, PhotoPes) → proportion of negative photos on a given day;


Data
1926-2018数据来源于Getty Images，日度情绪数据；使用WSJ数据的文献支撑：$\color{blue}{Shiller\ (2015)}$、$\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$、$\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013)}$00268-3/sbref0032)；



Data from 1926–2018 sourced from Getty Images; daily sentiment data; literature supporting the use of WSJ data: $\color{blue}{Shiller\ (2015)}$, $\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$, $\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013)}$00268-3/sbref0032);


Finding
PhotoPes具有投资者情绪代理的特征

首先，检验PhotoPes与美国主要股指和交易所交易基金（ETF）的关系：
  - $\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.\ (1990JPE)}$行为模型预计投资者情绪应当预测市场收益反转【当情绪高（低）时，非理性投资者将增加（减少）他们对资产的需求，从而推高（下跌）价格，偏离基本面。但由于套利的限制1;$\color{blue}{Pontiff\ (1996QJE)}$、$\color{blue}{Shleifer\ and\ Vishny\ (1997JF)}$】；然而，随时间推移，理性的投资者将利用错误定价，导致价格回到基本水平。
  - PhotoPes与次日市场收益呈负相关，与剩余交易周的市场收益呈正相关。该反转凸显了本文衡量标准对收益的$\color{red}{非信息性影响}$；
其次，照片悲观情绪与文字悲观情绪（TextPes）显著相关
  - 表明这两个变量所捕捉的信息类型存在一些共性；
  - 研究照片和文本中蕴含的悲观情绪如何相互作用后，发现新闻照片中的悲观情绪和新闻文本中的悲观情绪可以相互替代；
  - 实证表明$\color{red}{在照片显著的时期，照片会从文字中捕获注意力}$。
第三，深入了解新闻和金融市场背景下，哪类信息通过照片传播更有效：
  - 相较基线时期，恐惧情绪高涨时期照片中蕴含的悲观情绪的系数大两倍以上，而文本信息的系数则基本保持不变。即与文字相比，照片在传递创伤性新闻方面更为有效（$\color{blue}{Chemtob\ et\ al.,\ 1999JTS}$）；
  - 高度恐慌时期，照片对市场收益的影响最为显著；
第四，进一步验证PhotoPes作为投资者情绪代理的有效性，表明其对难以套利的股票影响更大：
  - 基于套利成本高的股票对投资者情绪冲击最敏感的预测（$\color{blue}{Baker\ and\ Wurgler,\ 2006}$），本文构建基于firm idiosyncratic volatility和size的投资组合；
  - 实证发现，PhotoPes对idiosyncratic volatility最高和size最小投资组合的收益影响最大；
第五，更好地理解PhotoPes与市场回报相关的渠道：
  - PhotoPes值的高低可预测次日异常交易量的增加，该证据进一步验证PhotoPes能够捕捉投资者情绪（$\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$）；
最后，稳健性检验表明，即使在控制了极端收益之后，主要结果对不同的可变结构标准仍然可靠，PhotoPes生成了显著样本外$R^2$；



PhotoPes exhibits characteristics of an investor sentiment proxy

First, examining the relationship between PhotoPes and major U.S. stock indices and exchange-traded funds (ETFs):
  - The behavioral model of $\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.\ (1990JPE)}$ predicts that investor sentiment should forecast market return reversals [when sentiment is high (low), irrational investors increase (decrease) their demand for assets, pushing prices up (down) away from fundamentals. However, due to limits to arbitrage 1; $\color{blue}{Pontiff\ (1996QJE)}$, $\color{blue}{Shleifer\ and\ Vishny\ (1997JF)}$]; however, over time, rational investors exploit the mispricing, causing prices to revert to fundamental levels.
  - PhotoPes is negatively correlated with next-day market returns and positively correlated with market returns for the rest of the trading week. This reversal highlights the $\color{red}{non-informational\ impact}$ of the measure on returns;
Second, photo pessimism is significantly correlated with text pessimism (TextPes)
  - indicating some commonality in the type of information captured by the two variables;
  - After examining how pessimism embedded in photos and text interact, the findings show that pessimism in news photos and news text are substitutes;
  - Empirical evidence shows that $\color{red}{during\ periods\ when\ photos\ are\ salient,\ photos\ capture\ attention\ from\ text}$.
Third, gaining deeper insight into which type of information is more effectively communicated through photos in the context of news and financial markets:
  - Compared to baseline periods, the coefficient on photo-embedded pessimism during periods of heightened fear is more than twice as large, while the coefficient on text information remains largely unchanged. That is, compared to text, photos are more effective at conveying traumatic news ($\color{blue}{Chemtob\ et\ al.,\ 1999JTS}$);
  - During periods of high fear, the impact of photos on market returns is most significant;
Fourth, further validating the effectiveness of PhotoPes as an investor sentiment proxy, showing its greater impact on stocks that are difficult to arbitrage:
  - Based on the prediction that stocks with high arbitrage costs are most sensitive to investor sentiment shocks ($\color{blue}{Baker\ and\ Wurgler,\ 2006}$), the paper constructs portfolios based on firm idiosyncratic volatility and size;
  - Empirical findings show that PhotoPes has the greatest impact on returns of portfolios with the highest idiosyncratic volatility and the smallest size;
Fifth, better understanding the channels through which PhotoPes relates to market returns:
  - High or low PhotoPes values predict increased abnormal trading volume the next day, providing further evidence that PhotoPes captures investor sentiment ($\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$);
Finally, robustness tests show that even after controlling for extreme returns, the main results remain robust to different variable construction criteria, and PhotoPes generates significant out-of-sample $R^2$;



 1.  有限套利或称套利限制是指由于风险、成本、信息不对称和制度性约束等因素的影响，使得套利者的套利行为受到限制。Limited arbitrage, or limits to arbitrage, refers to how risk, cost, information asymmetry, and institutional constraints restrict arbitrageurs’ ability to arbitrage. &#8617;

Literature ExtensionsRelated to Investor Sentiment Literature
鉴于投资者情绪的多维性，研究人员一直在寻找不同的方法来衡量投资者情绪（$\color{blue}{Zhou,\ 2018ARFE}$）；
使用新闻（$\color{blue}{Tetlock,\ 2007JF}$）、谷歌搜索数据（$\color{blue}{Da\ et\ al.,\ 2015RFS}$）、推特数据（$\color{blue}{Chen\ et\ al.,\ 2014RFS}$）、公司财务报告（$\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald,\ 2011JF}$；$\color{blue}{Jiang\ et\ al.,\ 2019JFE}$）、天气（$\color{blue}{Hirshleifer\ and\ Shumway,\ 2003JF}$）和体育赛事（$\color{blue}{Edmans\ et\ al.,\ 2007JF}$）代表投资者情绪（$\color{blue}{Hirshleifer,\ 2001JF}$）；



Given the multidimensional nature of investor sentiment, researchers have been seeking different approaches to measure it ($\color{blue}{Zhou,\ 2018ARFE}$);
Using news ($\color{blue}{Tetlock,\ 2007JF}$), Google search data ($\color{blue}{Da\ et\ al.,\ 2015RFS}$), Twitter data ($\color{blue}{Chen\ et\ al.,\ 2014RFS}$), corporate financial reports ($\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald,\ 2011JF}$; $\color{blue}{Jiang\ et\ al.,\ 2019JFE}$), weather ($\color{blue}{Hirshleifer\ and\ Shumway,\ 2003JF}$), and sports events ($\color{blue}{Edmans\ et\ al.,\ 2007JF}$) to proxy for investor sentiment ($\color{blue}{Hirshleifer,\ 2001JF}$);


Extending Investor Sentiment and News Literature
新闻是投资者信念的可信替代物，因为新闻界有需求方动机来迎合读者的信念（$\color{blue}{Shiller,\ 2005IE}$）。
$\color{blue}{Mullainathan\ and\ Shleifer\ (2005AER)}$总结了传播学、心理学、记忆和信息处理方面的文献，这些文献支持人们从与其信念一致的内容中获得效用的观点;
$\color{blue}{Gentzkow\ and\ Shapiro\ (2010Econ)}$为这一理论提供了实证证据，具体而言媒体的倾向性在很大程度上归因于消费者的偏好；
$\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$的$\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013JF)}$00268-3/sbref0032)研究表明，新闻文本中蕴含的情绪可以预测市场收益和交易量；
本文通过揭示新闻照片中包含与金融市场相关的内容，进一步扩展文献；



News is a credible proxy for investor beliefs because the news industry has demand-side incentives to cater to readers' beliefs ($\color{blue}{Shiller,\ 2005IE}$).
$\color{blue}{Mullainathan\ and\ Shleifer\ (2005AER)}$ summarize the literature in communications, psychology, memory, and information processing that supports the view that people derive utility from content consistent with their beliefs;
$\color{blue}{Gentzkow\ and\ Shapiro\ (2010Econ)}$ provide empirical evidence for this theory, specifically that media slant is largely attributable to consumer preferences;
Studies by $\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$ and $\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013JF)}$00268-3/sbref0032) show that sentiment embedded in news text can predict market returns and trading volume;
This paper extends the literature by revealing that news photos contain content relevant to financial markets;


Extending Visual Stimuli Psychology to Finance and Economics
关于新闻中视觉刺激的证据不一

一方面，图片优势效应（$\color{green}{picture\ \ superiority\ \ effect}$）是心理学中的一个已知概念，是指图片比文字更容易被回忆起的现象（$\color{blue}{Nelson\ et\ al.,\ 1976JEPHLM}$；$\color{blue}{Paivio,\ 1991Book}$）;
  - $\color{blue}{Newhagen\ and\ Reeves\ (1992JoC)}$将图片优势效应延伸到了新闻媒体，发现新闻中的视觉内容比新闻中的文字内容更容易被回忆；
  - 此外，$\color{blue}{Garcia\ and\ Stark\ (1991Book)}$以及$\color{blue}{Powell\ et\ al.\ (2015JoC)}$发现，图片在新闻中起到吸引注意力的作用；

另一方面，研究人员发现，当信息简单易懂时，视觉内容最为有效，而当信息复杂时，文字内容最为有效（$\color{blue}{Chaiken\ and\ Eagly,\ 1976JPSP}$）；
本文以金融决策为背景，对以上两方面文献进行调和；



Evidence on visual stimuli in news is mixed

On one hand, the picture superiority effect ($\color{green}{picture\ \ superiority\ \ effect}$) is a well-known concept in psychology, referring to the phenomenon that pictures are more easily recalled than words ($\color{blue}{Nelson\ et\ al.,\ 1976JEPHLM}$; $\color{blue}{Paivio,\ 1991Book}$);
  - $\color{blue}{Newhagen\ and\ Reeves\ (1992JoC)}$ extended the picture superiority effect to news media, finding that visual content in news is more easily recalled than textual content;
  - Furthermore, $\color{blue}{Garcia\ and\ Stark\ (1991Book)}$ and $\color{blue}{Powell\ et\ al.\ (2015JoC)}$ found that pictures serve as attention-grabbing elements in news;

On the other hand, researchers found that visual content is most effective when information is simple and easy to understand, while textual content is most effective when information is complex ($\color{blue}{Chaiken\ and\ Eagly,\ 1976JPSP}$);
This paper reconciles these two strands of literature in the context of financial decision-making;


Extending Visual Content Prediction in Financial Markets
一些研究记录了一张照片如何能够预测重要结果，如政治选举、个人贷款决策、公司市值和首席执行官薪酬（ $\color{blue}{Todorov\ et\ al.,\ 2005Science}$；$\color{blue}{Duarte \ et\ al.,\ 2012RFS}$；$\color{blue}{Halford\ and\ Hsu,\ 2020FR}$；$\color{blue}{Graham\ et\ al.,\ 2017MS}$）；

+ $\color{blue}{Bazley\ et\ al.\ (2021MS)}$记录了用红色显示财务信息如何降低投资者的风险偏好和乐观情绪；
+ $\color{blue}{Blankespoor\ et\ al.\ (2017JAR)}$展示了视频演示中对管理层的看法与公司价值的关系；
+ 本文首次利用机器学习从新闻照片中开发出投资者情绪代理预测股市收益；



Several studies have documented how a single photo can predict important outcomes such as political elections, personal loan decisions, firm market value, and CEO compensation ($\color{blue}{Todorov\ et\ al.,\ 2005Science}$; $\color{blue}{Duarte \ et\ al.,\ 2012RFS}$; $\color{blue}{Halford\ and\ Hsu,\ 2020FR}$; $\color{blue}{Graham\ et\ al.,\ 2017MS}$);

+ $\color{blue}{Bazley\ et\ al.\ (2021MS)}$ document how displaying financial information in red reduces investors' risk appetite and optimism;
+ $\color{blue}{Blankespoor\ et\ al.\ (2017JAR)}$ show the relationship between perceptions of management in video presentations and firm value;
+ This paper is the first to use machine learning to develop an investor sentiment proxy from news photos for predicting stock market returns;


DataPhoto classificationThe Primary Task of ML Photo Classification Models
CNN 是一种深度神经网络，可用于照片分类（$\color{blue}{Krizhevsky\ et\ al.,\ 2012ANIPS}$），最近的研究利用CNN照片分类模型：
  - 通过分析卫星图像识别太阳能电池板的安装（$\color{blue}{Yu\ et\ al.,\ 2019Jonle}$30570-1.pdf)）、奴隶营的位置（$\color{blue}{Scoles,\ 2019Science}$）以及欠发达国家的贫困程度（$\color{blue}{Jean\ et\ al.,\ 2016Science}$）；
  - 与本文类似，$\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI)}$也采用 CNN 进行图像情感分析，并在社交媒体的照片上取得了很高的准确率；



CNN is a type of deep neural network applicable to photo classification ($\color{blue}{Krizhevsky\ et\ al.,\ 2012ANIPS}$), and recent studies have utilized CNN photo classification models to:
  - Identify solar panel installations by analyzing satellite images ($\color{blue}{Yu\ et\ al.,\ 2019Jonle}$30570-1.pdf)), locate slave camps ($\color{blue}{Scoles,\ 2019Science}$), and assess poverty levels in underdeveloped countries ($\color{blue}{Jean\ et\ al.,\ 2016Science}$);
  - Similar to this paper, $\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI)}$ also employ CNN for image sentiment analysis and achieve high accuracy on social media photos;


Building a Model to Predict Photo-Induced Investor Sentiment
基于Google Inception (v3) ($\color{blue}{Szegedy\ et\ al.,\ 2016PIEEECCVPR)}$建立一个照片分类模型
  - Google Inception (v3) 是一个CNN模型，在ImageNet学术竞赛ILSVRC（ImageNet Large-Scale Visual Recognition Challenge，ImageNet大规模视觉识别挑战赛）中，它在1000个类别的照片分类方面表现出色，并被广泛应用于实践和研究中23；

TensorFlow是谷歌大脑团队开发的一个开源软件库，是机器学习应用的常用工具，提供了一个预训练的谷歌 Inception (v3) 模型
  - 从预训练Google Inception (v3) 模型（在ImageNet数据集上训练）入手，利用迁移学习针对本文特定应用对模型进行微调；
  - 预训练的Google Inception (v3) 有1000个不同的类别，其初始目的为：ILSVRC；
  - 【从头开始训练照片分类模型需要大量的训练样本，而且计算成本很高，133 1167 张预先标记的图片训练而成】通过迁移学习，重新利用预训练模型中存储的领域知识，只需将最后的全连接层替换为具有所需类别数量的新层，并用更少的训练样本重新训练最后全连接层的参数，轻松构建出本文所需模型（$\color{blue}{Yang\ et\ al.,\ 2013ML}$）；
  - 微调模型输出照片具有正面情感的概率和照片具有负面情感的概率；



Building a photo classification model based on Google Inception (v3) ($\color{blue}{Szegedy\ et\ al.,\ 2016PIEEECCVPR)}$)
  - Google Inception (v3) is a CNN model that excels at photo classification across 1,000 categories in the ImageNet academic competition ILSVRC (ImageNet Large-Scale Visual Recognition Challenge) and has been widely adopted in practice and research 23;

TensorFlow is an open-source software library developed by Google Brain, a common tool for machine learning applications, which provides a pre-trained Google Inception (v3) model
  - Starting from a pre-trained Google Inception (v3) model (trained on the ImageNet dataset) and fine-tuning the model for this paper's specific application via transfer learning;
  - The pre-trained Google Inception (v3) has 1,000 different categories, originally designed for ILSVRC;
  - [Training a photo classification model from scratch requires a large number of training samples and is computationally expensive, trained on 1,331,167 pre-labeled images] Through transfer learning, domain knowledge stored in the pre-trained model is repurposed by simply replacing the final fully connected layer with a new layer containing the desired number of categories and retraining the parameters of the last fully connected layer with fewer training samples, easily constructing the model needed for this paper ($\color{blue}{Yang\ et\ al.,\ 2013ML}$);
  - The fine-tuned model outputs the probability that a photo has positive sentiment and the probability that it has negative sentiment;



 2. 在来自ImageNet数据集的验证集上，前五名和前一名的错误率分别为 3.5% 和 17.3%。前一错误率是指模型没有将正确类别作为其最高预测概率的时间百分比。前五名错误率是指该模型未将正确类别作为其概率排名前五的预测结果的时间百分比。On the validation set from the ImageNet dataset, the top-5 and top-1 error rates are 3.5% and 17.3%, respectively. The top-1 error rate is the percentage of time the model does not rank the correct category as its highest probability prediction. The top-5 error rate is the percentage of time the model does not rank the correct category among its top five probability predictions. &#8617;


