Why a Finer Classification Model Was Not Developed
首先，更精细的分类需要主观判断。大多数文本情感分析，如$\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald\ (2011JF)}$的分析，都是对词语进行二元分类（如正面词语和负面词语） 4。
其次，本文尝试创建一个具有更精细类别的照片分类模型，但模型无法收敛，因为其无法检测出不同细分类之间的明显区别。



First, finer classification requires subjective judgment. Most text sentiment analyses, such as that of $\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald\ (2011JF)}$, perform binary classification of words (e.g., positive and negative words) 4.
Second, the authors attempted to create a photo classification model with finer categories, but the model failed to converge because it could not detect clear distinctions between different subcategories.



 4. 例如，”疾病”和”崩溃”显然是负面的，但其负面程度却不太明显。语境和个人对单词本身的主观解释也会影响负面情绪的程度。For example, “disease” and “crash” are clearly negative, but the degree of negativity is less obvious. Context and subjective interpretation of the words themselves also affect the degree of negative sentiment. &#8617;

Transfer Learning
迁移学习需要一个由情感标签照片组成的训练集。
本文使用DeepSent数据集进行训练5， 由$\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI)}$收集并按情感标记的照片集。
使用DeepSent数据集的主要优势在于，情感标签是通过众包网站（如MTurk） 验证的，以确保标签的正确性6。【为了提高可靠性，作者使用MTurk调查的所有五位参与者都同意照片情感的照片。这一限制将训练样本减少到 882 张照片。】
该模型使用0.01的学习率和500个学习步骤进行训练7。将训练批次大小设置为100张照片，保留10%的训练照片作为验证样本，20%的训练照片作为测试样本（照片随机分配到各集合）8。
训练集是训练过程中用于调整最终全连接层权重的照片集。验证集是一组照片，不用于调整最后一个完全连接层的权重，但它们的唯一目的是通过验证训练准确性的任何提高不会以牺牲超出的代价来帮助最大限度地减少过度拟合。样本性能。最后，测试集是模型在训练过程中从未见过的一组照片，用于计算模型的最终准确度得分。除了使用验证集来限制过度拟合之外，我们还通过使用增强技术（例如翻转、缩放）并在模型中添加正则化技术（例如 dropout 和标签平滑）来扩大训练集（Szegedy 等人，2016）。
训练集是在训练过程中用于调整最后全连接层权重的照片集。验证集是不用于调整最后全连接层权重的照片集，但其唯一目的是通过验证训练精度的提高是否以牺牲样本外性能为代价，从而帮助最大限度地减少过拟合。最后，测试集是模型在训练过程中从未见过的一组照片，用于计算模型的最终准确率得分。除了使用验证集来限制过拟合外，作者还通过使用增强技术（e.g., flip, scale）以及在模型中添加正则化技术（如dropout and label smoothing ）来扩大训练集（$\color{blue}{Szegedy\ et\ al.,\ 2016PIEEECCVPR}$）。



Transfer learning requires a training set composed of sentiment-labeled photos.
This paper uses the DeepSent dataset for training 5, a collection of photos gathered and labeled by sentiment by $\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI)}$.
The main advantage of using the DeepSent dataset is that sentiment labels are validated through crowdsourcing platforms (e.g., MTurk) to ensure label accuracy 6. [To enhance reliability, the authors use only photos for which all five MTurk survey participants agreed on the photo's sentiment. This restriction reduces the training sample to 882 photos.]
The model is trained with a learning rate of 0.01 and 500 training steps 7. The training batch size is set to 100 photos, with 10% of training photos reserved as validation samples and 20% as test samples (photos are randomly assigned to each set) 8.
The training set is the set of photos used to adjust the weights of the final fully connected layer during training. The validation set is a set of photos not used to adjust the weights of the final fully connected layer; its sole purpose is to help minimize overfitting by verifying whether improvements in training accuracy come at the cost of out-of-sample performance. Finally, the test set is a set of photos the model has never seen during training, used to calculate the model's final accuracy score. In addition to using the validation set to limit overfitting, the authors also expand the training set by using augmentation techniques (e.g., flip, scale) and adding regularization techniques (e.g., dropout and label smoothing) to the model ($\color{blue}{Szegedy\ et\ al.,\ 2016PIEEECCVPR}$).



