Model Validation (Human-Labeled WSJ Data)
问题：DeepSent训练集中的照片来自社交媒体，可能与 WSJ 样本中的专业新闻照片类型不太相似，使用 DeepSent训练集训练的模型可能无法对专业照片进行准确分类。

解决：从WSJ样本中随机选取100张照片，并对每张照片进行分类（分类工作由五个人在MTurk中预先完成）11。通过模型对照片进行预测，并将预测结果与从MTurk收集到的回复进行比较。作者将分析结果总结为以下混淆矩阵12：


Problem: The photos in the DeepSent training set come from social media and may not closely resemble the professional news photos in the WSJ sample. A model trained on the DeepSent training set may not accurately classify professional photos.

Solution: 100 photos were randomly selected from the WSJ sample, and each photo was classified (classification was pre-completed by five workers on MTurk)11. The model was used to generate predictions, which were then compared with responses collected from MTurk. The authors summarized the results in the following confusion matrix12:




根据上述混淆矩阵，计算模型在对WSJ的专业新闻照片样本进行分类时的表现。准确率为 76.0%；召回率为92.8%；精确率为77.1%；F1为84.2%。鉴于样本中存在不平衡的类别，因此关注F1至关重要。准确率、召回率、精确率和 F1 数值与$\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI) }$基于使用DeepSent数据集训练的照片分类算法所报告的数值接近（他们的结果汇总见 $\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI) }$的表1）。总体而言，该表显示本文使用DeepSent训练集训练的模型在新闻照片分类方面表现良好。


Based on the confusion matrix above, the model's performance in classifying WSJ professional news photos is computed. Accuracy is 76.0%; recall is 92.8%; precision is 77.1%; F1 is 84.2%. Given the imbalanced classes in the sample, focusing on F1 is crucial. The accuracy, recall, precision, and F1 values are close to those reported by $\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI) }$ based on photo classification algorithms trained using the DeepSent dataset (their results are summarized in Table 1 of $\color{blue}{You\ et\ al.\ (2015PAAAICAI) }$). Overall, the table demonstrates that the model trained on the DeepSent training set performs well in classifying news photos.



