The Wall Street Journal sample

WSJ关注重大事件，目标受众是对经济和金融市场特别感兴趣的读者。WSJ为订户提供在线访问过去文章的服务，最早可追溯到1997年12月。但是，2008年9月之前的文章很少附带照片。缺少2008年9月之前照片的原因之一是，《华尔街日报》并不拥有许多照片的版权，而是从Associated Press, Reuters, and Getty Images等其他新闻和媒体机构获得了照片的有限授权。一旦许可证到期，照片就会被删除。

从WSJ的2008年9月至2020年9月期间以下版面收集了每篇文章的标题和摘要、相关照片以及文章发表的时间戳：”Business,” “Economy,” “Markets,” “Politics,” and “Opinion”。只要是与经济相关的国际话题（如 “Asia Business”）均会收录，这些栏目报道与公司或行业相关的重大事件以及总体市场状况。

**共收集148823篇文章，时间跨度为3048个交易日。使用第2.1节中讨论的照片分类模型对这些照片进行情感分类。**



The WSJ focuses on major events, targeting readers with a particular interest in the economy and financial markets. The WSJ provides subscribers with online access to past articles dating back to December 1997. However, articles before September 2008 rarely include photos. One reason for the absence of photos before September 2008 is that the WSJ does not own the copyright to many photos but obtained limited licenses from other news and media agencies such as Associated Press, Reuters, and Getty Images. Once the licenses expired, the photos were removed.

The title and summary of each article, accompanying photos, and publication timestamps were collected from the following WSJ sections from September 2008 to September 2020: “Business,” “Economy,” “Markets,” “Politics,” and “Opinion.” Economy-related international topics (e.g., “Asia Business”) were also included. These sections cover major events related to companies or industries and overall market conditions.

**A total of 148,823 articles were collected, spanning 3,048 trading days. The photo classification model discussed in Section 2.1 was used to classify the sentiment of these photos.**


Variable construction$PhotoPes$
主要变量"$PhotoPes$"的计算方法为：预测在特定日期为负数的照片所占比例。第$t$天的$PhotoPes$计算公式为：


The main variable "$PhotoPes$" is calculated as the proportion of photos predicted to be negative on a given date. The formula for $PhotoPes$ on day $t$ is:



PhotoPes_t=\frac{\sum_i(Neg_{it})}{n_t}
其中$Neg_{it}$是一个指标变量，表示第$t$天的照片$i$是否会产生负面情绪。分母$n_t$对应的是$t$日的照片数量。网站（https://www.kuntara.net/）提供相关数据。

$PhotoPes$并非简单的二元衡量标准。虽然单张照片被分为负面或正面，但$PhotoPes$是一个连续的测量值。与负面照片较少的日子相比，负面照片较多的日子的$PhotoPes$值较高，这与文献中许多情感度量方法的理念相同。本文使用另一个版本的$PhotoPes$展示基线结果，该版本使用预测可能性 （$PhotoPes$）代替指标变量$Neg_{it}$。$\color{blue}{表 2\ Panel\ B}$显示，结果一致。如果将指标变量 ($Neg_{it}$) 的临界值从50%调整到 55%，结果一致
)的临界值从 50% 调整为 55%，我们的结果仍然成立（$\color{blue}{表A 2\ Panel\ A}$）。


where $Neg_{it}$ is an indicator variable for whether photo $i$ on day $t$ conveys negative sentiment. The denominator $n_t$ corresponds to the number of photos on day $t$. The data are available at https://www.kuntara.net/.

$PhotoPes$ is not a simple binary measure. Although individual photos are classified as either negative or positive, $PhotoPes$ is a continuous measure. Days with more negative photos have higher $PhotoPes$ values compared to days with fewer negative photos, consistent with the logic of many sentiment measures in the literature. The authors also present baseline results using an alternative version of $PhotoPes$ that substitutes predicted probabilities for the indicator variable $Neg_{it}$. $\color{blue}{Table\ 2\ Panel\ B}$ shows that the results are consistent. Results also hold when adjusting the threshold of the indicator variable ($Neg_{it}$) from 50% to 55% ($\color{blue}{Table\ A2\ Panel\ A}$).



$TextPes$

**本文目标之一是比较照片和文字中蕴含的悲观情绪。**受[$\color{blue}{Manela\ and\ Moreira\ (2017JFE)}$](http://refhub.elsevier.com/S0304-405X(21)00268-3/sbref0047)以及[$\color{blue}{Cong\ et\ al.\ (2018SSRN)}$](https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3307057)的启发，作者分析了文章的标题和摘要。从概念上讲，用来识别照片中悲观情绪的机器学习方法包括特征之间的高度非线性关系。为了便于对照片和文本中的悲观情绪进行公平比较，**避免使用词典方法对文本进行分类**。相反，使用斯坦福大学**CoreNLP软件中的情感工具来评估每个句子中的悲观情绪，并将文本中所有句子的平均悲观情绪得分作为文章的悲观情绪得分**，即$TextNeg$（来源：https://stanfordnlp.github.io/CoreNLP/）。

该情感工具以递归神经张量网络（RNTN）为基础，在包含215154个短语的数据集上进行训练，这些短语带有细粒度的情感标签（标度：{“ 负面 “ = 1; “ 中性 “ = 0.5; “ 正面 “ = 0}）。*该RNTN模型在短语方面表现尤为突出，短语准确率高达 85.4%*（[$\color{blue}{Socher\ et\ al.,\ 2013PCEMNLP}$](https://aclanthology.org/D13-1170.pdf)）。由于WSJ文章的标题和摘要部分通常都很简短，因此该工具非常适合。$TextPes$的计算公式如下：



**One of the paper's objectives is to compare the pessimism embedded in photos and text.** Inspired by [$\color{blue}{Manela\ and\ Moreira\ (2017JFE)}$](http://refhub.elsevier.com/S0304-405X(21)00268-3/sbref0047) and [$\color{blue}{Cong\ et\ al.\ (2018SSRN)}$](https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3307057), the authors analyzed article titles and summaries. Conceptually, the machine learning methods used to identify pessimism in photos involve highly nonlinear relationships among features. To facilitate a fair comparison of pessimism in photos and text, **dictionary-based methods are avoided for text classification**. Instead, the **sentiment tool in Stanford's CoreNLP software is used to evaluate pessimism in each sentence, and the average pessimism score across all sentences serves as the article's pessimism score**, i.e., $TextNeg$ (source: https://stanfordnlp.github.io/CoreNLP/).

The sentiment tool is based on a Recursive Neural Tensor Network (RNTN), trained on a dataset of 215,154 phrases with fine-grained sentiment labels (scale: {“Negative” = 1; “Neutral” = 0.5; “Positive” = 0}). *The RNTN model performs particularly well on phrases, achieving a phrase-level accuracy of 85.4%* ([$\color{blue}{Socher\ et\ al.,\ 2013PCEMNLP}$](https://aclanthology.org/D13-1170.pdf)). Since WSJ article titles and summaries are typically short, this tool is well-suited. The formula for $TextPes$ is:



TextPes_t=\frac{\sum_i(TextNeg_{it})}{n_t},

其中$TextNeg_{it}$是CoreNLP模型中第$t$天每篇文章$i$的悲观分数。分母$n_t$对应于日期$t$中的文章数量。$PhotoPes$和 $TextPes$进行1%水平缩尾处理。结果在不进行缩尾处理的情况下保持不变（$\color{blue}{表A 2\ Panel\ B}$）。

基于RNTN方法而不是基于字典的方法，原因如下：

- 首先，本文用来识别图像中情感的方法包含了特征之间的高度非线性关系，而**对文本采用基本方法会让图像捕捉到更微妙的情感特征，从而使结果对作者有利，而对文本采用简单的方法则无法捕捉到这些情感特征**。*例如，字典方法对”好”和”很棒”等积极词给予相同的权重，并且不考虑上下文和单词组合，而RNTN方法则考虑这一点，因此使用具有相当复杂性的方法提取情感合适。*
- 其次，本文分析的是文章的标题和摘要部分，比全文短得多。**字典方法最适合10-K或完整新闻稿等长文本，因为其避免任何单词与字典中的单词重叠的情况**（[$\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald,\ 2011JF}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2010.01625.x)）。*本文数据中92.47%的文章标题和摘要部分不包含任何属于Loughran和McDonald词典的净负面或正面词汇。相比之下，使用机器学习方法，只有63.66%的标题和文章摘要部分包含中性情绪。*



where $TextNeg_{it}$ is the pessimism score for article $i$ on day $t$ from the CoreNLP model. The denominator $n_t$ corresponds to the number of articles on day $t$. $PhotoPes$ and $TextPes$ are winsorized at the 1% level. Results remain unchanged without winsorization ($\color{blue}{Table\ A2\ Panel\ B}$).

The RNTN-based method rather than a dictionary-based method is used for the following reasons:

- First, the method used to identify sentiment in images involves highly nonlinear relationships among features, and **using a basic method for text would allow images to capture more nuanced sentiment features, thereby biasing results in the authors' favor, while a simpler text method would fail to capture these features**. *For example, dictionary methods assign equal weight to positive words like “good” and “great” and do not consider context or word combinations, whereas the RNTN method accounts for this, making a comparably sophisticated method appropriate for extracting sentiment.*
- Second, the paper analyzes article titles and summaries, which are much shorter than full articles. **Dictionary methods are best suited for long texts such as 10-Ks or full press releases, as they avoid the situation where no words overlap with words in the dictionary** ([$\color{blue}{Loughran\ and\ McDonald,\ 2011JF}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2010.01625.x)). *In this paper's data, 92.47% of article titles and summaries contain no net negative or positive words from the Loughran and McDonald dictionary. In contrast, using the machine learning method, only 63.66% of titles and summaries contain neutral sentiment.*


Descriptive statistics

$\color{blue}{表1\ Panel\ A}$报告了悲观变量的汇总统计量。从2008年9月到2020年9月，有3048个交易日。平均而言，$PhotoPes$为 0.228，即22.8%的照片在某一天会出现负面情绪。平均而言，$TextPes$为0.686，表明平均而言，文章的标题和摘要文本由负面句子组成（Scale：{“Negative”= 1；”Neutral “= 0.5；”Positive”= 0}）。所有变量都有明显的一阶自相关性，因此具有持久性（在测试中解决了自相关性问题）。

$\color{blue}{表1\ Panel\ B}$报告主要美国股指和ETF的汇总统计数据。$\color{blue}{表1\ Panel\ C}$报告了$PhotoPes$与$TextPes$的关系。计算$PhotoPes$和$TextPes$之间的成对相关性和对应$p$值，$PhotoPes$和$TextPes$呈正相关（相关系数=0.079，$p$值 < 0.01）。然而，相关性不是很高，这表明照片中存在的一些信息与WSJ文章标题和摘要部分中的文本不同。在文章层面，62.65%的文章文字和图片语气一致。$\color{blue}{图2}$显示$PhotoPes$和$TextPes$的每日和每月频率的时间序列，在恐慌情绪高涨的时期，包括2008年至2011年的次贷危机和2020年的COVID-19危机，这两个序列都会出现较大的峰值。例如，2011年两个变量的峰值特别大，可以归因于美国与基地组织之间的高度紧张，从美国政府于 2011年5月9日处决基地组织头目就可见一斑。此外，2011年3月11日日本东北地区发生地震和海啸后，美国西海岸也发出了海啸警报。 2011年3月16日，美国食品批发价格上涨3.9%，创1974年11月以来最大单月涨幅。有关通胀失控的传言只会让情况变得更糟。综上所述，重大新闻事件往往伴随着悲观照片，而这些照片正是我们的衡量指标。最后，与正常时期相比，**市场动荡时期$PhotoPes$和$TextPes$更加接近**[^ 13]。



$\color{blue}{Table\ 1\ Panel\ A}$ reports summary statistics for the pessimism variables. From September 2008 to September 2020, there are 3,048 trading days. On average, $PhotoPes$ is 0.228, meaning 22.8% of photos on a given day convey negative sentiment. On average, $TextPes$ is 0.686, indicating that article titles and summaries are on average composed of negative sentences (Scale: {“Negative” = 1; “Neutral” = 0.5; “Positive” = 0}). All variables exhibit significant first-order autocorrelation and are therefore persistent (autocorrelation is addressed in the tests).

$\color{blue}{Table\ 1\ Panel\ B}$ reports summary statistics for major U.S. stock indices and ETFs. $\color{blue}{Table\ 1\ Panel\ C}$ reports the relationship between $PhotoPes$ and $TextPes$. The pairwise correlation and corresponding $p$-value between $PhotoPes$ and $TextPes$ show a positive correlation (correlation = 0.079, $p$-value < 0.01). However, the correlation is not very high, suggesting that some information present in photos differs from the text in WSJ article titles and summaries. At the article level, 62.65% of articles have consistent tone between text and photos. $\color{blue}{Figure\ 2}$ shows the time series of $PhotoPes$ and $TextPes$ at daily and monthly frequencies. During periods of heightened pessimism, including the 2008-2011 subprime crisis and the 2020 COVID-19 crisis, both series exhibit large spikes. For example, particularly large peaks in both variables in 2011 can be attributed to heightened tensions between the U.S. and al-Qaeda, as evidenced by the U.S. government's execution of the al-Qaeda leader on May 9, 2011. Additionally, following the earthquake and tsunami in northeastern Japan on March 11, 2011, tsunami warnings were issued for the U.S. West Coast. On March 16, 2011, U.S. wholesale food prices rose 3.9%, the largest single-month increase since November 1974. Rumors of runaway inflation only made matters worse. In summary, major news events tend to be accompanied by pessimistic photos, which are precisely what our measure captures. Finally, **$PhotoPes$ and $TextPes$ are more closely aligned during periods of market turbulence** compared to normal periods[^ 13].



 13. 市场动荡期间，$PhotoPes$和$TextPes$之间的相关系数最高。相关性在2008年第四季度达到峰值，约为0.5，然后在 2009年1月下降至0.2。同样，在2020年第二季度，新冠疫情期间，相关性跃升至 0.36。 &#8617;



Results

行为模型通过做出两个假设打破理性投资者和市场效率模型：

- 首先，行为模型考虑到一些投资者是非理性的并且能够影响价格（[$\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/261703)）。诸如推断（[$\color{blue}{Tversky\ and\ Kahneman,\ 1983}$](https://psycnet.apa.org/record/1984-03110-001)）和过度自信（[$\color{blue}{Fischhoff\ et\ al.,\ 1977}$](https://psycnet.apa.org/journals/xhp/3/4/552/)）等偏差可能会导致非理性投资者增加对金融资产的需求，从而推动价格超出经济基本面。
- 其次，套利的限制阻止理性投资者全面、立即纠正价格偏离基本面的情况（[$\color{blue}{Pontiff,\ 1996QJE}$](https://academic.oup.com/qje/article-abstract/111/4/1135/1932203)；[$\color{blue}{Shleifer\ and\ Vishny,\ 1997JF}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1997.tb03807.x)）。行为模型的主要预测之一是市场回报反转：当积极（消极）情绪飙升时，非理性投资者将增加（减少）资产需求，推动价格远离基本水平。行为模型预测，需求的增加（减少）将导致更高（更低）的收益，随着市场修正至其基本水平，这种回报将随着时间的推移而反转。



Behavioral models break the rational investor and market efficiency framework by making two assumptions:

- First, behavioral models account for the fact that some investors are irrational and can influence prices ([$\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/261703)). Biases such as representativeness ([$\color{blue}{Tversky\ and\ Kahneman,\ 1983}$](https://psycnet.apa.org/record/1984-03110-001)) and overconfidence ([$\color{blue}{Fischhoff\ et\ al.,\ 1977}$](https://psycnet.apa.org/journals/xhp/3/4/552/)) can lead irrational investors to increase demand for financial assets, pushing prices beyond economic fundamentals.
- Second, limits to arbitrage prevent rational investors from fully and immediately correcting price deviations from fundamentals ([$\color{blue}{Pontiff,\ 1996QJE}$](https://academic.oup.com/qje/article-abstract/111/4/1135/1932203); [$\color{blue}{Shleifer\ and\ Vishny,\ 1997JF}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1997.tb03807.x)). A key prediction of behavioral models is market return reversal: when positive (negative) sentiment surges, irrational investors increase (decrease) asset demand, pushing prices away from fundamental levels. Behavioral models predict that this increase (decrease) in demand leads to higher (lower) returns, which reverse over time as the market corrects to its fundamental level.


News sentiment embedded in photos and text

本节讨论主要结果：

- 首先，证明**照片中嵌入的悲观情绪预示着市场收益的反转**，这与行为模型的预测一致（[$\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/261703)）；
- 其次，研究**照片中嵌入的悲观度如何与文本中嵌入的悲观度相互作用**；
- 第三，探讨**与文字相比，哪种类型的新闻内容通过照片更有效地传播**；
- 第四，**构建了三种现实世界的交易策略，以强调分析新闻照片的益处**。



This section discusses the main results:

- First, demonstrating that **pessimism embedded in photos predicts market return reversals**, consistent with the predictions of behavioral models ([$\color{blue}{De\ Long\ et\ al.,\ 1990JPE}$](https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/261703));
- Second, examining **how pessimism embedded in photos interacts with pessimism embedded in text**;
- Third, exploring **which types of news content are more effectively transmitted through photos compared to text**;
- Fourth, **constructing three real-world trading strategies to highlight the benefits of analyzing news photos**.


The impact of $PhotoPes$ on market returns

$\color{blue}{表2}$是$PhotoPes$对滞后的市场收益进行时间序列回归的主要结果，参考 [$\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01232.x)和[$\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013JF)}$](http://refhub.elsevier.com/S0304-405X(21)00268-3/sbref0032)。具体而言，使用[$\color{blue}{Newey\ and\ West\ (1987Econ)}$](https://www.jstor.org/stable/1913610?origin=crossref)的$t$统计进行以下计算：



$\color{blue}{Table\ 2}$ presents the main results of time-series regressions of $PhotoPes$ on lagged market returns, following [$\color{blue}{Tetlock\ (2007JF)}$](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01232.x) and [$\color{blue}{Garcia\ (2013JF)}$](http://refhub.elsevier.com/S0304-405X(21)00268-3/sbref0032). Specifically, using [$\color{blue}{Newey\ and\ West\ (1987Econ)}$](https://www.jstor.org/stable/1913610?origin=crossref) $t$-statistics, the following regression is estimated:



R_{t}=\beta_{1}L5(PhotoPes_{t})+\beta_{2}L5(R_{t})+\beta_{3}L5\Big(R_{t}^{2}\Big)+\beta_{4}X_{t}+\varepsilon_{t},

其中，$R_{t}$表示日度对数收益

